  "body": "To be similar to the design in caddy it defines the base directory/path to run directives from.\n\nThe syntax would look like this:\n\n```\n.:2053 {                                                                                                                                 \n  root /var/public/dns\n  file zone2.db zone2 # file would be located at /var/public/dns/zone2.db\n}\n```\n\nSome additional considerations:\n- Default path would be the current working directory where coredns was run.\n- Relative paths use the working directory as base.\n\nStarting coredns in /usr/bin for example would have the following paths associated:\nno root set ->  **/usr/bin** (default path)\n**root /var/public/dns** -> **/var/public/dns** (overwritten)\n**root dns** -> **/usr/bin/dns** (relative using default as base)\n",
